# What is an RDD, really?

- **RDD** = Resilient Distributed Dataset — the original Spark abstraction. Every DataFrame compiles down to it.
- **Resilient** — lost partitions recomputed from lineage, not a replica.
- **Distributed** — partitioned across executor memory on many machines.
- **Dataset** — a collection of any objects — **no schema, no columns**.
- Immutable · lazy · schema-free · typed at runtime.
